page.title: 10Mr Woods Retired Commuter
page.content: Mr Harry Woods who has lived in Corringham for twenty years, is eighty years of age. His wife is sixty-nine and called Margerie. They have three grown up sons aged 34, 36, 38.Their names are Richard, Malcolm and Robin. Since they moved to Corringham the village has changed from being mainly agricultualto catering for managerial people. Mr Woods did not work in Corringham, he was a workshop super-intendant on the REME estate. He now visits Gainsborough three times a week for shopping and welfare activities. Mr Woods has lived in the same bungalow (which he designed himself) since he came to Corringham.It is quite spaceous and set in a 1/4 acre of garden. Mr Woods is a keen gardener.
